fields.name: Arduino UNO R4 WiFi
fields.description: The Arduino UNO R4 WiFi merges the RA4M1 microprocessor from Renesas with the ESP32-S3 from Espressif, creating an all-in-one tool for makers with enhanced processing power and a diverse array of new peripherals.

fields.name: Arduino Giga R1 WiFi
fields.description: A new board joins the Arduino family, and it's the most powerful ever designed for makers, engineers and creators: the GIGA R1 WiFi! Bridging you from great fun to amazing performance, it opens the door to infinite possibilities in robotics, IoT, music, computer vision, digital fabrication, and any kind of projects involving machines, interfaces, and real-time processing - in the same form factor as the popular Mega and Due boards.

fields.name: Arduino Uno Rev3
fields.description: The Arduino UNO is one of the best boards to get started with electronics and coding. If this is your first experience tinkering with the platform, the UNO is the most robust board you can start playing with. The UNO is the most used and documented board of the whole Arduino family.

fields.name: Arduino Nano ESP32 (with headers)
fields.description: The new member of our iconic Arduino Nano family, the Nano ESP32. This board brings all the power of the well-known ESP32-S3 with the full support of the Arduino ecosystem, allowing makers to explore the world of Arduino and MicroPython without any blocker. Just unleash your creativity and start building for the next IoT project.

fields.name: Arduino Nano Every (With Headers)
fields.description: Turn your ideas into a reality quickly with the new Arduino Nano Every. This version has headers pre-soldered.

fields.name: Arduino UNO R4 Minima
fields.description: Introducing the Arduino UNO R4 Minima! This board boasts the RA4M1 microprocessor from Renesas, delivering increased processing power, expanded memory, and additional peripherals. And the best part? It stays true to the reliable UNO form factor and operates at a practical 5V voltage.

fields.name: Arduino Mega 2560 Rev3
fields.description: The 8-bit Arduino board with 54 digital pins, 16 analogue inputs and 4 serial ports.

fields.name: Terminal Shield for Arduino Mega
fields.description: You're probably using an Arduino Mega because you have a LOT of devices to hook up to your project, and this shield is just itching to help you with that!

fields.name: Arduino Nano (with headers)
fields.description: The classic Arduino Nano is the smallest Arduino board to build your projects with.

fields.name: Screw Terminal Shield for Arduino UNO
fields.description: This is a screw terminal shield specifically designed for the Arduino UNO or UNO compatible boards. The board allows you to quickly build and prototype your own circuit.

fields.name: USB-A to USB Mini-B Cable - Black
fields.description: This USB to Mini-B USB Cable is available in a range of lengths and has been tested with some of our favourite microcontrollers to ensure it reliably passes both data and power.

fields.name: Clear Protective Case for Arduino Uno
fields.description: This protective case has been designed specifically for the Arduino Uno and is available in a range of different colours - this is the clear version!

fields.name: Arduino Motor Shield Rev3
fields.description: The Arduino Motor Shield allows your Arduino to drive DC and stepper motors, relays and solenoids.

fields.name: Adafruit HUZZAH32 - ESP32 Feather Board
fields.description: Aww yeah, it's the Feather you have been waiting for! The HUZZAH32 is our ESP32-based Feather, made with the official WROOM32 module. We packed everything you love about Feathers: built in USB-to-Serial converter, automatic bootloader reset, Lithium Ion/Polymer charger, and just about all of the GPIOs brought out so you can use it with any of our Feather Wings. We have other boards in the Feather family, check 'em out here.

fields.name: Arduino Ethernet Shield 2
fields.description: The Arduino Ethernet Shield 2 connects your Arduino to the internet in mere minutes. Just plug this module onto your Arduino Board, connect it to your network with an RJ45 cable (not included) and follow a few simple steps to start controlling your world through the internet.

fields.name: Arduino MKR Zero
fields.description: MKR ZERO has an on-board SD connector with dedicated SPI interfaces (SPI1) that allows you to play with MUSIC files with no extra hardware!

fields.name: 0.3MP OV7675 20-pin DVP Camera Module for Arduino GIGA R1 WiFi
fields.description: This camera module is based on the OmniVision 0.3MP OV7675 image sensor, which excels in image capture with its advanced features and exceptional performance. Its pixel array captures intricate details with precision and clarity, while its low-light imaging capabilities reveal hidden elements in challenging lighting conditions.

fields.name: Maker UNO
fields.description: The Maker UNO is an Arduino compatible board specially designed to simplify building projects. Coding & electronics is made easy and affordable with 12 built in LEDs, a built-in buzzer and a button.

fields.name: Arduino Proto Shield Rev3 (Uno Size)
fields.description: Make your projects rock solid with the Prototyping Shield. It makes it easy for you to design custom circuits and solder electronics directly to it.

fields.name: Gravity: 1602 LCD Keypad Shield For Arduino
fields.description: This is a very popular LCD Keypad shield for Arduino and other variants. It includes a 2x16 LCD display and 6 momentary push buttons. Pins 4, 5, 6, 7, 8, 9 and 10 are used to interface with the LCD. Just one Analog Pin 0 is used to read the five push buttons. The LCD shield supports contrast adjustment and back-lit on/off functions. It also exposes five analog pins with DFRobot color code for easy analog sensor plugging and display. The on board LED indicates power on.

fields.name: Raspberry Pi 5
fields.description: Featuring a 64-bit quad-core Arm Cortex-A76 processor running at 2.4GHz, Raspberry Pi 5 delivers a 2-3x increase in CPU performance relative to Raspberry Pi 4! Raspberry Pi 5 also brings with it a huge list of great new features and improvements, making this the best Raspberry Pi yet!

fields.name: Active Cooler for Raspberry Pi 5
fields.description: The Raspberry Pi Active Cooler provides an alternative cooling solution for users who wish to use their Raspberry Pi 5 under sustained heavy load without a case (but you might want to add one of our fancy Active Cooler covers for protection!)

fields.name: Raspberry Pi Pico
fields.description: The Raspberry Pi Pico is an entirely new type of microcontroller from Raspberry Pi. Small, affordable and flexible - it's great for learning to code with MicroPython!

fields.name: Raspberry Pi 5 Case
fields.description: The official Raspberry Pi 5 case is a refinement of the Raspberry Pi 4 case, with a number of improvements and thermal features to accommodate the footprint and peak power consumption of Raspberry Pi 5.

fields.name: Three 40A/240V Relays RS485 Daisy-chainable HAT for Raspberry Pi
fields.description: The Three 40A/240V Relays RS485 Daisy-channable HAT is designed for use with the Raspberry Pi. It features three heavy-duty relays that can handle up to 40A and 240V each, suitable for controlling three-phase industrial loads. The card can be daisy-chained up to 32 units through an RS485 port and is equipped with pluggable connectors, an on-board processor, and LED indicators

fields.name: Pico Air Monitoring Expansion
fields.description: The Air Monitoring Expansion for Raspberry Pi Pico is an open-source, portable sensor that measures suspended particulate quantity by mass. It operates at 5V and features a digital laser dust sensor (PMSA003) and a built-in 0.91 inch OLED display providing information on air particulate matter (PM1.0, PM2.5, PM10) via digital output. Communication is done through UART (serial), and it offers external GPIO Breakout Pins for connecting sensors.

fields.name: OLED/LCD Triple Screen HAT for Raspberry Pi
fields.description: Designed to integrate with Raspberry Pi series boards, this HAT has a 2 inch IPS LCD main screen with a built-in ST7789VW driver chip. It offers a clear display with a resolution of 240 x 320. The screen uses an SPI interface for communication and boasts a wide viewing angle. It features a 262K colour display, making it ideal for vibrant and detailed visuals. Included with the main screen are two 0.96 inch OLED screens, each powered by an SSD1315 driver chip. These screens communicate via the I2C interface and feature a lovely blue display colour. With a resolution of 128 x 64, they are perfect for displaying key information, status indicators, or small graphics.

fields.name: PoE HAT for Raspberry Pi 5 with Cooling Fan (5V and 12V outputs)
fields.description: This PoE HAT has been designed specifically for Raspberry Pi 5 (the new PoE pin position) and is compliant with IEEE 802.3af/at standards, enabling you to power your Raspberry Pi 5 directly through a power-injected ethernet cable.

fields.name: Official UK Raspberry Pi 4 Power Supply (5.1V 3A)
fields.description: The official Raspberry Pi USB-C 15.3W power supply. Built specifically for the Raspberry Pi 4 Model B

fields.name: Raspberry Pi Zero 2 W
fields.description: The Raspberry Pi Zero 2 W is the latest board in the Raspberry Pi Zero family, with a quad-core processor offering a 40% increase in single-threaded performance and 5x times more multi-threaded performance than the previous single-core Raspberry Pi Zero W!

fields.name: Raspberry Pi 4 Model B
fields.description: The Raspberry Pi 4 is a powerful and feature-rich Raspberry Pi, an incredible improvement on previous boards.

fields.name: Raspberry Pi Camera Module 3
fields.description: The Raspberry Pi Camera Module 3 is the latest entry in the Official Raspberry Pi range of camera modules, offering a new 12 Megapixel Sony IMX708 image sensor, powered autofocus, improved low-light sensitivity and HDR (High Dynamic Range) support for your Raspberry Pi projects!

fields.name: SSD to USB 3.0 Cable for Raspberry Pi
fields.description: After a lot of testing, we finally found an SSD (SATA) to USB 3.0 cable that works really well with the Raspberry Pi 4! Great for USB Booting or even just adding fast SSD storage for your media, documents and files.

fields.name: Raspberry Pi PoE+ HAT
fields.description: The Raspberry Pi PoE+ HAT is a new version of the original Raspberry Pi PoE HAT, now with 5V 4A output for the most demanding Raspberry Pi applications! It is designed to replace the original PoE HAT in all new and existing designs and meets all requirements of the IEEE 802.3af (802.3at Type 1) specifications.

fields.name: Cover for Raspberry Pi Active Cooler
fields.description: Your Raspberry Pi 5 is now cold chilly thanks to your Active Cooler - but does it look cool? No, because you haven't got one of our snazzy covers yet!

fields.name: Official Raspberry Pi MicroSD Adapter
fields.description: The Official Raspberry Pi MicroSD card adapter!

fields.name: Raspberry Pi Camera Module 3 NoIR
fields.description: The Raspberry Pi Camera Module 3 NoIR is the latest entry in the Official Raspberry Pi range of camera modules, offering a new 12 Megapixel Sony IMX708 image sensor, powered autofocus, improved low-light sensitivity and HDR (High Dynamic Range) support for your Raspberry Pi projects!

fields.name: Raspberry Pi 3 Model A+
fields.description: The Raspberry Pi 3 Model A+ is a compact yet powerful Raspberry Pi, part of the Raspberry Pi 3 range of boards.

fields.name: GPIO Reference Board (40 Pin)
fields.description: This cute little GPIO reference board from ModMyPi allows you to quickly and easily distinguish between the 40 different pins of the Raspberry Pi!

fields.name: Debug Cable for Raspberry Pi Pico
fields.description: This cable allows you to use the 3-pin JST-SH debug port on the Raspberry Pi Pico H for SWD (Serial Wire Debug) debugging.

fields.name: micro:bit V2.2
fields.description: Meet the new micro:bit V2.2 - an improved version of the original micro:bit featuring a built-in speaker, microphone, touch sensor and more computing power! This listing is for the single micro:bit V2.2 board.

fields.name: Silicon Protective Case for micro:bit V2
fields.description: This affordable micro:bit silicone case is compatible with the brand new micro:bit V2 board and comes in three fun colours (select colour above).

fields.name: Black Frosted Case for micro:bit V2
fields.description: This black frosted case is a great home for your shiny new micro:bit V2!

fields.name: micro:bit 2xAA Battery Holder with ON/OFF Switch
fields.description: The micro:bit can be powered with a micro-USB cable when loading code, or you can use a battery holder for projects on the move (or maybe just the sofa!).

fields.name: JST-PH Battery Extension Cable - 500mm
fields.description: By popular demand, we now have a handy extension cord for all of our JST-terminated battery packs (such as our LiIon/LiPoly and 3xAAA holders). One end has a JST-PH socket, and the other end has a matching plug. Between the two, 500mm of color coded wire. Handy for wearable projects where you may want the battery pack far from your Flora but useful in many other situations where you need a little more space.

fields.name: Green Frosted Case for micro:bit V2
fields.description: This green frosted case is a great home for your shiny new micro:bit V2!

fields.name: Ring:bit Car V2 for micro:bit
fields.description: The Ring:bit Car (v2) is a small DIY smart car driven by the BBC micro:bit (not included) and Ring:bit board (included)! Play and programming come together with this cute servo-driven robot, which can be programmed with simple drag-and-drop blocks within the MakeCode Editor.

fields.name: MI:pro Protector Case for the BBC micro:bit V1 & V2
fields.description: This Kitronik MI:pro Protector Case for the BBC micro:bit has been designed to work with both the original micro:bit V1 and the new micro:bit V2. The case continues in the traditions of Kitronik's earlier cases - designed to keep the micro:bit safe, fully useable, and to offer the freedom of not being tethered to a computer.

fields.name: :MOVE Motor for the BBC micro:bit
fields.description: Develop your coding skills with the Kitronik :MOVE Motor for micro:bit, a fun introduction to buggies and robotics.

fields.name: Grove WiFi 8266 - IoT for micro:bit, Pico & More
fields.description: The Grove WiFi 8266 module is designed to enable your micro:bit (when combined with an EDU:BIT), Raspberry Pi Pico and Maker Pi RP2040 (and other controllers too!) to send and receive data over the internet through a Wi-Fi network.

fields.name: Noise Add-On Pack for Kitronik Inventor's Kit for micro:bit
fields.description: Learn how to bend sound to your will with the Noise Pack add-on for the Kitronik Inventors Kit for the BBC micro:bit!

fields.name: Prong Soil Moisture Sensor for BBC micro:bit
fields.description: The Prong soil moisture sensor for BBC microbit is a sensor board that can be directly mounted to a BBC micro:bit to monitor the moisture present in soil. The two conductive tines are placed into the soil. Any water or moisture in the soil will conduct to give an analogue voltage that can be read by the BBC micro:bit.

fields.name: Adafruit NeoPixel LED Strip w/ Alligator Clips - 30 LEDs/meter (1 Meter - BLACK)
fields.description: Adding glowy color to your projects has never been easier: no more soldering or stripping wires, clip 'em on and glow! This Adafruit NeoPixel LED Strip with Alligator Clips has 30 total LEDs in a 30 LED per meter spacing, and is 1 meter long, in classy Adafruit Black. It's not too long, but has lots of glowing action. Perfect for use with a Circuit Playground, Circuit Playground Express, micro:bit or any other microcontroller board where you don't want to noodle with a breadboard and wires.

fields.name: REKA:BIT Robotics Board for micro:bit
fields.description: The REKA:BIT is a compact robotics expansion board for your BBC micro:bit (not included), providing a huge range of useful features, ports and onboard protection to help you make awesome micro:bit robotics projects. It's the smaller sibling of the popular EDU:BIT.

fields.name: Inventor's Kit for the micro:bit
fields.description: Get more from the micro:bit with Kitronik's incredible Inventor's kit! The simple way to learn about creating circuits and code.

fields.name: Inventor's Kit for the Raspberry Pi Pico
fields.description: The Kitronik Inventor's Kit for the Raspberry Pi Pico provides a fantastic way of learning how to construct and control electronic circuits with the Pico and MicroPython.

fields.name: Inventor's Kit for the Arduino
fields.description: The Kitronik Inventor's Kit for Arduino is a great way to get started with programming and hardware interaction with the Arduino. This Inventor's Kit contains everything you need to complete 10 experiments including using LEDs, motors, Phototransistors and capacitors.

fields.name: Noise Add-On Pack for Kitronik Inventor's Kit for micro:bit
fields.description: Learn how to bend sound to your will with the Noise Pack add-on for the Kitronik Inventors Kit for the BBC micro:bit!

fields.name: Digital Logic Add-On Pack for Kitronik Inventor's Kit for micro:bit
fields.description: Learn to think logically with the Digital Logic Add-On for the Kitronik Inventor's kit for micro:bit!

fields.name: Inventor HAT Mini
fields.description: The Inventor HAT Mini helps transform a Raspberry Pi computer into a robot, prop, kinetic sculpture, creepy automaton or other exciting moving things. Want to drive a couple of fancy motors with encoders (or hook up standard motors with jumper wires)? Yep! Add up to four servos? Sure? Attach a little speaker so you can make noise? No problem!

fields.name: ZIP LED Add-On Pack for Kitronik Inventor's Kit for micro:bit
fields.description: This add-on pack for the Kitronik Inventors Kit for the BBC micro:bit provides the perfect way to learn about the wonderful world of ZIP LEDs. These LEDs are simple to control and can be used to produce a whole range of fantastic colours.

fields.name: Inventor 2040 W (Pico W Aboard)
fields.description: An all-in-one board for making battery-powered contraptions that can move, (optionally) make noise, and talk to the internet, with a Raspberry Pi Pico W built-in!

fields.name: SparkFun Inventor's Kit for RedBot
fields.description: The SparkFun Inventor's Kit for RedBot is a great way to get started with two motor robotics and sensor integration using the Arduino programming language. The SIK for RedBot includes everything you need to complete nine circuits that will teach you how to drive your RedBot, have it follow lines, control it remotely, and more. This kit doesn't require previous programming or electronics experience but it is recommended that you possess an understanding of or desire to learn about robotics.

fields.name: Arduino Inventor's Guide
fields.description: The Arduino microcontroller makes it easy to learn about electronics, but it can be hard to know where to start. The 10 projects in this book will teach you to build, code, and invent with the super-smart Arduino and a handful of parts.

fields.name: Grove Inventor Kit for micro:bit
fields.description: The Grove Inventor Kit for Micro:bit is an accessible addition to your micro:bit, offering a variety of new possibilities. It features the Grove shield for micro:bit v2.0, which allows you to connect different Grove modules like sensors and displays to your micro:bit easily, without needing to solder or use jump wires.

fields.name: BBC Doctor Who HighFive Inventor Coding Kit - Premium Version
fields.description: The BBC Doctor Who HiFive Inventor (“HiFive”) is a pocket-sized Internet of Things (IoT) computer, designed for makers, students, and educators who want to learn computer programming, a vital 21st-century skill that uses artificial intelligence, robotics, and more!

fields.name: Inventors Kit for the BBC micro:bit - Python version
fields.description: The Kitronik Inventor's Kit - Python version for the BBC micro:bit (not included) is a great way to get started with programming and hardware interaction with the micro:bit.

fields.name: Arduino Oplà IOT Kit
fields.description: Add smart technology to your home and workplace with the first open programmable IoT platform that allows you to build custom IoT devices!

fields.name: micro:Maqueen Plus V2 (18650) - Advanced STEM Education Robot for micro:bit
fields.description: This is the Maqueen Plus V2, the latest version of the STEM educational robot from DFRobot for the BBC micro:bit (not included). Now optimised with more expansion ports, a larger capacity power supply and a larger body.

fields.name: Bit:Bot XL Robot Kit for the micro:bit
fields.description: The Bit:Bot XL takes the much-loved BitBot to the next level! 4Tronix have made several changes, some subtle, some not so subtle, to give a much-improved experience of using and working with the BitBot.

fields.name: TPBot - Smart Car Robot Kit for BBC micro:bit
fields.description: The TPBot is a smart car robot kit for the BBC micro:bit with a premium building brick compatible ABS chassis, RGB programmable headlights, ultrasonic distance (object avoidance) and line tracking sensors.

fields.name: :MOVE Mat - Robot Line Following and Activity Maps (A1 size)
fields.description: The :MOVE mat line is an accessory for the :MOVE Motor and :MOVE mini robots. It can be used just for fun, or as part of a project in the classroom. The mat is double-sided, with a line following track on one side and a mock-up of a town on the other.

fields.name: MiniBit Robot for the micro:bit
fields.description: An easy, simple and ready-to-go robot for your BBC micro:bit.

fields.name: 2WD miniQ Robot Chassis
fields.description: 2WD miniQ robotic platform is especially designed for students and hobbyists. It's versatile and small, suitable for most indoors applications. It features high quality and powerful metal gear motors which make it a speedy robot. It is ideal for maze competition and educational courses, and is very easy to assemble, check out our assembly video below. Only requires 8 screws to get the job done and you can use our sample codes on our Wiki pages.  If you are planning to get started building a robot, as a proof of concept, its small body and light weight makes it a great choice. This robot can easily be used and tested on a desk or small area, easily assembled and expanded. An extra set of stand off and screws might come handy. It's round shape helps when moving around objects, avoiding obstruction. The platform has convenient drillings that helps placing sensors or other screwable parts like custom designed casing.

fields.name: AlphaBot2 Robot Kit for BBC micro:bit
fields.description: The AlphaBot2 robot kit is designed to use with the BBC micro:bit (not included) and features a great list of popular robot features including line tracking, obstacle avoiding, ultrasonic ranging, Bluetooth remote control (via Android app), RGB LEDs, a buzzer and more!

fields.name: DIY Spider Robot
fields.description: With the DIY Spider Robot, you can design and manufacture your own robotic creature!

fields.name: KitiBot Tracked Robot Kit for BBC micro:bit
fields.description: The KitiBot is a fun full-metal tracked robot kit for the BBC micro:bit (not included). Using the micro:bit as the brains of the robot along with the chassis, controller board (with LEDs and Buzzer!), tracks, sensors and accessories provided in this kit, you can create an awesome micro:bit robot!

fields.name: Zumo 32U4 Robot (Assembled with 75:1 HP Motors)
fields.description: The Pololu Zumo 32U4 robot is a versatile tracked robot based on the Arduino-compatible ATmega32U4 MCU. It includes two 75:1 HP micro metal gearmotors along with integrated dual motor drivers, an LCD, quadrature encoders, line sensors, side and front proximity sensors for detecting objects, and a full IMU for detecting impacts and tracking orientation.

fields.name: Devastator Tank Mobile Robot Platform (Metal DC Gear Motor)
MeArm Maker Kit V3
fields.description: The MeArm Maker Kit V3 is an easy-to-build robot arm kit that's designed to get children (and adults!) learning about technology, engineering and programming. It's been expressly designed to be easy to build (age 11+) and use.

fields.name: Pan-Tilt HAT
fields.description: Please ensure you select the correct option (above). Only the full kit comes complete with servos.

fields.name: Heatsink for Raspberry Pi Zero 2
fields.description: If you're planning to push your Raspberry Pi Zero 2 to the max, you may want to keep an eye on CPU temperatures as the new RP3A0 system-in-package runs a little warmer than the previous generation of Raspberry Pi Zero CPUs.

fields.name: Flex Cable for Raspberry Pi Camera or Display - 300mm
fields.description: This cable will let you swap out the stock 150mm long flex cable from a Raspberry Pi Camera, HQ camera or Raspberry Pi Display, for a different size. Works great, just carefully open the connector on your Raspberry Pi 4/3/2 and slip this one in.

fields.name: STEMMA QT / Qwiic Compatible JST-SH 4-Pin Cable (50mm)
fields.description: This 4-wire cable is 50mm long and comes complete with JST-SH female 4-pin connectors on both ends which are compatible with Adaruit STEMMA QT and SparkFun Qwiic connectors and modules.

fields.name: SNES-style Raspberry Pi Compatible USB Gamepad /Controller
fields.description: Gaming on the Raspberry Pi has never felt so nostalgic!

fields.name: NES-Style Raspberry Pi Compatible USB Gamepad / Controller
fields.description: If you're going REALLY retro with your Raspberry Pi retro gaming project, our SNES style USB controllers may be way too modern for you old schoolers. If you'd rather keep things a bit more 1983 than 1990, these white NES-style USB controllers might be a good option for you.

fields.name: 120-Piece Ultimate Jumper Bumper Pack (Dupont Wire)
fields.description: The ultimate jumper cable ('dupont' wire) kit, containing 120pcs of rainbow-coloured jumper wires in all the formats you could possibly need for breadboard prototyping!

fields.name: Full-Size Breadboard - White
fields.description: This is a 'full-size' white breadboard with 830 tie points. Good for small and medium projects.

fields.name: Half-Size Breadboard - White
fields.description: Half-size breadboards are handy for most projects, and these versions include interlocking sections meaning you can join lots of these together to scale up for larger projects.

fields.name: Multifunction Wire Strippers
fields.description: We've upgraded our basic 'adjustable' wire strippers to these multi-sized wire strippers.

fields.name: Engineer PA-06 Pro Wire Strippers (AWG16-AWG30)
fields.description: Engineer has been manufacturing high-quality Japanese precision tools since 1948. If you're looking for the very best precision hand tools for your projects - look no further. Check out our range of Engineer tools here!

fields.name: Helping Third Hand Magnifier W/Magnifying Glass Tool (MZ101)
fields.description: The classic 'third hand tool', as seen on every desk! We have one next to our Panavise jr, they complement each other well. This tool is good for holding small PCBs and wires for tinning or soldering to parts.

fields.name: Spudger - Double Sided Prying Tool
fields.description: Is there something missing from your tool kit or workstation? Are you having trouble figuring out which elusive tool it is that you're lacking? Perhaps it's a spudger! 'A what?' A s-p-u-d-g-e-r! It's a prying tool that has a wide flat-head screwdriver-like end that extends as a wedge, used to separate pressure-fit plastic components without causing damage during separation.

fields.name: 38 In 1 Interchangeable precise tool set
fields.description: 38 in 1 Multifunctional suit screwdriver.

fields.name: 65 Piece Ratchet Screwdriver and Tool Bit Set
fields.description: Look, over there at that thing! Take it apart! You can now attack just about every kind of box or enclosure that needs undoing with this ratchet screwdriver set. This set is fine quality and excels at disassembling and assembling larger hardware and makes a good companion to our smaller 38-piece set.What drew us to this tool box is its comprehensive selection of bits, the two rubber screwdriver handles (one small and one large, neither are thin or slippery), that the large screwdriver has a built in ratchet, the magnetic bit holder (which is not hollow so you don't have to get annoyed when bits fall through into the handle, tough CR-V alloy steel bits, and the very nice box to hold it all! Each bit is also stamped with the name/size. Both handles come with an extension so you can get into nooks & crannies.

fields.name: Precision Diagonal Cutters
fields.description: These precision diagonal micro cutters are a popular choice for makers thanks to their versatility and small size.

fields.name: Miniware TS101 Smart Soldering Iron
fields.description: The TS101 Smart Soldering Iron is the next generation of soldering iron from Miniware, the same folks who brought us the popular TS100 and TS80P.

fields.name: Engineer SS-02 Professional Silicone-Tip Solder Sucker
fields.description: Engineer has been manufacturing high-quality Japanese precision tools since 1948. If you're looking for the very best precision hand tools for your projects - look no further. Check out our full range of Engineer tools here!

fields.name: 3D Print Deburring Tool + 10x Blades
fields.description: This tool is a must-have for any anyone looking to clean up rough edges on their 3D prints.

fields.name: Engineer Neji-Saurus Screw Removal Pliers (PZ-57/PZ-58)
fields.description: Engineer has been manufacturing high-quality Japanese precision tools since 1948. If you're looking for the very best precision hand tools for your projects - look no further. Check out our range of Engineer tools here!

fields.name: Long Nose Flat Tip Pliers
fields.description: Useful for bending wire and working in tight spaces that regular pliers couldn't access, these long nose pliers feature a flat tip (no grip) making them a gentler option when used with softer materials and wire insulation over the more traditional gripped versions. No more tearing up your cables!

fields.name: Antex XS25 Soldering Iron (UK Plug)
fields.description: Everyone needs a good soldering iron and this quality Antex model is perfect for all levels of maker!

fields.name: Antex Lead Free Solder - 4m Tube
fields.description: Lead Free Solder!
